<div id='gazette_story'>
    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>YOU ARE CORDIALLY INVITED...</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20091029.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, October 29, 2009</b> &mdash;
    The invitations must have been delivered late at night because, even though Millsberry&#039;s residents woke to find a dark and mysterious scroll-invitation waiting on their doorstep, no one had seen or heard a thing (not even here at the <i>Gazette</i>).<br><br>The invitation reads: Your presence is requested in the Count Chocula Room, the Franken Berry Room, and the Boo Berry Room. From 10/29 to 11/04, visit the <a href="http://millsberry.com/campaigns/redLionManor2009/">Red Lion Manor</a> for spooky-fun games, treats, and surprises! <br><br>Around town, people were intrigued, spooked, and excited. Was <a href="http://millsberry.com/campaigns/redLionManor2009/">Franken Berry</a> a person? What was the <a href="http://millsberry.com/campaigns/redLionManor2009/">Boo Berry Room</a>? Would the <a href="http://millsberry.com/campaigns/redLionManor2009/">Count Chocula Room</a> be scary?! We sought out some answers from Mr. Combee, Millsberry&#039;s greenhouse keeper, and the first to visit <a href="http://millsberry.com/campaigns/redLionManor2009/">Red Lion Manor</a> in his eager effort to check out events around town. <br>
<br>
We found Mr. Combee returning from a shopping trip&mdash;wearing a long brown cape! (With all of the new Halloween merchandise for sale, the <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">stores</a> have been packed.) Combee gave us the scoop on his visit to the Manor, pulling out a spider wig from his shopping bag as he spoke. &quot;I don&#039;t want to spoil all of the surprises, but I encourage everyone to check out the <a href="http://millsberry.com/campaigns/redLionManor2009/">Red Lion Manor</a> for Halloween fun&mdash;especially since it&#039;s only here for one week! <br><br>&quot;Each room is dedicated to a different monster among Boo Berry, Franken Berry, and Count Chocula. These guys were discovered living in a castle back in 1971, and shortly thereafter they were asked to make delicious cereals. I loved them and their cereals as a kid&mdash;and now they&#039;re back so everyone in Millsberry can enjoy them too.&quot;  <br><br>Combee continued, &quot;In each room, there&#039;s a fun game you need to play in order to win a fabulous prize&mdash;like this Count Chocula costume! And, if you win all three games from all three rooms, you&#039;ll win a grand prize. I still need to go back and try to win one more game, and then I&#039;ll be able to get the grand prize!&quot;<br><br>We asked Combee if the Manor was haunted. He said, &quot;I don&#039;t think so. It&#039;s all silly-fun and no one should be frightened! Some of the rooms are dark, making it hard to find the things you need to for each game, but that&#039;s also the fun of it. And I just love how different each monster is. Boo Berry is a funny ghost who loves to spook Count Chocula. The Count has a single-fanged smile and has always lived in a castle. And Franken Berry loves pink and strawberries! (It&#039;s also a surprise to learn that, for such a big, chain-wearing monster, he&#039;s scared of his own shadow)!&quot;<br><br>So get in the Halloween spirit. In addition to trick-or-treating around town, get treated to even more over at the Manor, while learning about each monster and their cereal. And don&#039;t forget to check out the new costumes, and decorations available downtown for your home. There are also some favorite oldies from the past&mdash;back and on the rack!<br><br>And, after you&#039;ve gotten a taste of each room, answer our poll to vote for your favorite monster!
    </div>

